name: Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception
description: The Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception is a late 19th-century English Gothic revival church that serves as the cathedral of the Roman Catholic Diocese of Hong Kong.

name: St. Joseph's Church
description: St. Joseph's Chruch was built sometime in the early 1870s. A severe typhoon on 22nd September, 1874 razed the structure to the ground. Rebuilding took place and was completed two years later
